# Dollar amount formatting

All **human-readable** dollar amounts must use thousands separators (comma every three digits).

## Shared helper

Use `github.com/openshift-online/finops-tools/cli/internal/format`:

| Function | Use case | Example |
|----------|----------|---------|
| `FormatAmount(amount)` | Numeric part only, 2 decimals | `12,345,678.90` |
| `FormatMoney(amount, currency)` | CLI tables, HTML reports | `USD 1,234.50` |
| `FormatChartMoney(amount, currency)` | Chart axis labels (whole numbers when ≥ 1000) | `USD 7,927` |

Do not duplicate comma-insertion logic in commands, `output/`, or `report/`.

## When to apply

- Pretty-print CLI output (`cli/internal/output/`)
- HTML reports and embedded SVG charts (`cli/internal/report/`)
- Any new user-facing cost or currency strings

## When not to apply

- JSON, CSV, and API payloads: keep raw `float64` / full-precision strings
- Internal calculations and AWS API values

## Examples

```go
// ✅ GOOD
totalLine := fmt.Sprintf("%s %s", r.Currency, format.FormatAmount(r.Amount))
view.TotalFormatted = format.FormatMoney(r.Total, r.Currency)

// ❌ BAD
fmt.Sprintf("%s %.2f", cur, amount)
fmt.Sprintf("%.2f", amount)
```
